{% doc %}
  @prompt
    Create a **coffee subscription landing page** inspired by the structure and UX of Onyx Coffee Lab’s subscription page, but fully adapted to the **Unchained brand**.
    >
    > ### Brand & Tone
    >
    > * Brand name: **Unchained Coffee**
    > * Tone: **Bold, minimal, premium, Apple-style**
    > * Attitude: Transparent, rebellious, no fluff
    > * Core idea: *Unchained is a call to change the coffee chain*
    >
    > ### Page Goal
    >
    > Help customers easily subscribe to specialty coffee while clearly understanding:
    >
    > * What they get
    > * How it works
    > * Why it matters
    >
    > ---
    >
    > ### Page Structure (Required)
    >
    > #### 1. Hero Section
    >
    > * Headline: short, powerful, minimal
    >   Example:
    >   **“Never Run Out of Coffee. Change the Chain.”**
    > * Subheadline explaining value in one sentence:
    >   *Freshly roasted specialty coffee. Delivered on your schedule. Up to 70% goes directly to the producer.*
    >
    > ---
    >
    > #### 2. Choose Your Coffee
    >
    > * Selector for **Single Origin / Espresso / Drip / Limited Editions**
    > * Emphasize transparency and traceability
    >
    > ---
    >
    > #### 3. Choose Your Bag Size
    >
    > * Options: 10 oz / 12 oz / 2 lb / 5 lb
    > * Simple, clean UI language
    >
    > ---
    >
    > #### 4. Choose Your Delivery Schedule
    >
    > * Weekly
    > * Every 2 weeks
    > * Monthly
    > * Copy should highlight flexibility:
    >   *Skip, pause, or cancel anytime.*
    >
    > ---
    >
    > #### 5. Why Subscribe with Unchained
    >
    > Use short, scannable bullet points:
    >
    > * Fresh coffee, roasted weekly
    > * Direct trade. Radical transparency
    > * Up to **70% of revenue goes directly to small coffee growers**
    > * No contracts. No middlemen. No compromises
    >
    > ---
    >
    > ####
{% enddoc %}
